        <description>
GRaND was operated during Mars-Vesta cruise from 30-Nov-2009 to 7-Dec-2009. The report details acquisition of background counting data, assessment of instrument state of health and optimization of instrument settings. Interferences from the Ion Propulsion System with instrument operations are found to be negligible.

          It was adapted from the Dawn GRaND PDS3 BGO Data Processing document at the time the
          GRaND PDS3 archive was migrated to PDS4.
        </description>
